-- FACTBOX: Top 10 tech and media mergers
-- 
-- Fri Feb 1, 2008 1:44pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/01/us-yahoo-microsoft-mergers-idUSN0143732220080201

 

 (Reuters) - Microsoft Corp on Friday offered to buy Yahoo Inc for $44.6 billion in cash and stock, seeking to join forces against Internet leader Google Inc. 

 If Yahoo accepts the bid, the deal would be the fifth-largest in the technology, media and publishing sectors, according to Dealogic. The following list ranks the largest deals in that sector. 
BUYER                      TARGET                         PRICE 
America Online Inc         Time Warner Inc               $112.1 billion 
Comcast Corp               AT&T Broadband                 $60.7 billion 
AT&T Corp                  Tele-Communications Inc        $52.0 billion 
Viacom Inc                 CBS Corp                       $45.2 billion 
Microsoft Corp             Yahoo Inc                      $44.6 billion 
Bain Capital, TH Lee       Clear Channel Communications   $26.4 billion 
Lucent Technologies        Ascend Communications          $23.9 billion 
Clear Channel              AMFM Inc                       $21.6 billion 
Walt Disney Co             Capital Cities/ABC Inc         $20.0 billion 
Hewlett-Packard Co         Compaq Computer Corp           $18.7 billion 
SOURCE: Dealogic
